Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @baking potatoes{2} lengthways and pop them onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Rub the oil over the potatoes, then lay them cut-side down on the baking tray.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until tender and a knife slips in easily, ~{30-40%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the mince cooks, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1/2%can} in a #sieve{}.

Once the mince is cooked, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with salt and pepper.

Add the garlic and @Cajun spice mix{1%tsp} to the beef. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1} and @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{150%ml} for the sauce, then stir through the kidney beans.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

While the mince mixture simmers, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{40%g}.

Cut the @medium tomatoes{2} into 1cm chunks. Cut the @lime{1} into wedges.

In a large #bowl{}, combine a drizzle of oil with a good squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt, pepper and a pinch of sugar (if you have any), then add the tomatoes and mix well. Set aside for now.

Once the mince mixture is ready, season with salt, pepper and a squeeze of lime juice. Remove from the heat.

When you're almost ready to serve, reheat the mince if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Add the @baby leaf mix{20%g} to the bowl of tomatoes and toss together.

Transfer the baked potatoes to your plates, cut-side up. Add a knob of @butter{} to the potatoes if you'd like.

Spoon the Cajun beef over the top and sprinkle with the cheese, then garnish with lime wedges for squeezing over.

Serve the salad alongside to finish. Enjoy!